\subsection{Weight of a Hilbert modular form}
\begin{definition}\label{mf.hilbert.weight_vector}
\uses{mf.hilbert}
The **weight** of a {{ KNOWL('mf.hilbert', "Hilbert modular form") }} $f$ is the vector of positive integers $(k_1\ldots,k_n)$ occurring in the transformation formula for $f$. When the $k_i$ are all equal to $k \in \Z_{>0}$, we say $f$ has **parallel weight** $k$.
\end{definition}


